    },
    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.1",
          "pli": "“Rūpārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā rūparatā rūpasammuditā. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, gods and humans like sights, they love them and enjoy them. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.2",
          "pli": "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
          "en": "But when sights perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.3",
          "pli": "Saddārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā saddaratā saddasammuditā. ",
          "en": "Gods and humans like sounds … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.4",
          "pli": "Saddavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.5",
          "pli": "Gandhārāmā … ",
          "en": "smells … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.6",
          "pli": "rasārāmā … ",
          "en": "tastes … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.7",
          "pli": "phoṭṭhabbārāmā … ",
          "en": "touches … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.8",
          "pli": "dhammārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā dhammaratā dhammasammuditā. ",
          "en": "thoughts, they love them and enjoy them. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.9",
          "pli": "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti. ",
          "en": "But when thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.10",
          "pli": "Tathāgato ca kho, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho rūpānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na rūpārāmo na rūparato na rūpasammudito. ",
          "en": "The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sights, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.11",
          "pli": "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati. ",
          "en": "When sights perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.12",
          "pli": "Saddānaṃ … ",
          "en": "The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sounds … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.13",
          "pli": "gandhānaṃ … ",
          "en": "smells … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.14",
          "pli": "rasānaṃ … ",
          "en": "tastes … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.15",
          "pli": "phoṭṭhabbānaṃ … ",
          "en": "touches … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.16",
          "pli": "dhammānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na dhammārāmo, na dhammarato, na dhammasammudito. ",
          "en": "thoughts, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.17",
          "pli": "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati”. ",
          "en": "When thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.18",
          "pli": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
          "en": "That is what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:1.19",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: ",
          "en": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:2.1",
          "pli": "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā, ",
          "en": "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:2.2",
          "pli": "phassā dhammā ca kevalā; ",
          "en": "touches and thoughts, the lot of them—"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:2.3",
          "pli": "Iṭṭhā kantā manāpā ca, ",
          "en": "they’re likable, desirable, and pleasurable "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:2.4",
          "pli": "yāvatatthīti vuccati. ",
          "en": "as long as you can say that they exist. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:3.1",
          "pli": "Sadevakassa lokassa, ",
          "en": "In all the world with its gods, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:3.2",
          "pli": "ete vo sukhasammatā; ",
          "en": "this is reckoned as happiness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:3.3",
          "pli": "Yattha cete nirujjhanti, ",
          "en": "And where they cease "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:3.4",
          "pli": "taṃ tesaṃ dukkhasammataṃ. ",
          "en": "this is reckoned as suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:4.1",
          "pli": "Sukhaṃ diṭṭhamariyebhi, ",
          "en": "The noble ones have seen that happiness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:4.2",
          "pli": "sakkāyassa nirodhanaṃ; ",
          "en": "is the cessation of identity. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:4.3",
          "pli": "Paccanīkamidaṃ hoti, ",
          "en": "Those who see "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:4.4",
          "pli": "sabbalokena passataṃ. ",
          "en": "contradict the whole world. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:5.1",
          "pli": "Yaṃ pare sukhato āhu, ",
          "en": "What others say is happiness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:5.2",
          "pli": "tadariyā āhu dukkhato; ",
          "en": "the noble ones say is suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:5.3",
          "pli": "Yaṃ pare dukkhato āhu, ",
          "en": "What others say is suffering "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:5.4",
          "pli": "tadariyā sukhato vidū. ",
          "en": "the noble ones say is happiness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:6.1",
          "pli": "Passa dhammaṃ durājānaṃ, ",
          "en": "See, this teaching is hard to understand, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:6.2",
          "pli": "sammūḷhettha aviddasu; ",
          "en": "it confuses the ignorant. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:6.3",
          "pli": "Nivutānaṃ tamo hoti, ",
          "en": "Those who don’t see are closed off; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:6.4",
          "pli": "andhakāro apassataṃ. ",
          "en": "for them, all is blind darkness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:7.1",
          "pli": "Satañca vivaṭaṃ hoti, ",
          "en": "But those who see are open; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:7.2",
          "pli": "āloko passatāmiva; ",
          "en": "for the good, it is light. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:7.3",
          "pli": "Santike na vijānanti, ",
          "en": "Though it’s right there, the unskilled fools "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:7.4",
          "pli": "maggā dhammassa akovidā. ",
          "en": "don’t understand the teaching. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:8.1",
          "pli": "Bhavarāgaparetebhi, ",
          "en": "They’re mired in desire to be reborn, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:8.2",
          "pli": "bhavarāgānusārībhi; ",
          "en": "flowing along the stream of lives, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:8.3",
          "pli": "Māradheyyānupannehi, ",
          "en": "mired in Māra’s sovereignty: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:8.4",
          "pli": "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho. ",
          "en": "this teaching isn’t easy for them to understand. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:9.1",
          "pli": "Ko nu aññatra mariyebhi, ",
          "en": "Who, apart from the noble ones, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:9.2",
          "pli": "Padaṃ sambuddhumarahati; ",
          "en": "is qualified to understand this state? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:9.3",
          "pli": "Yaṃ padaṃ sammadaññāya, ",
          "en": "When they’ve rightly understood it, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:9.4",
          "pli": "Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti. ",
          "en": "they’re extinguished without defilements.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.136:9.5",
          "pli": "Tatiyaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
